<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>298807</id>
	<title>nsIBookmarksService::ResolveKeyword can make a better use of strings</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">ResolveKeyword is currently declared as</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">string resolveKeyword(in wstring aName, out wstring aPostData)</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">What it returns is actually in UTF-8 so that we'd better declare it as</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">AUTF8String resolveKeyword(in wstring aName, out AString aPostData)</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">With that, we can avoid ToNewUnicode and ToNewUTF8String in actual
implementations.Moreover, the string conversion across XPConnect will be done
properly instead of 'blind inflation'.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
